Load shifting is an electricity load management technique in which load demand is shifted from peak hours to off-peak hours of the day. 
Or in other words, load shifting simply means moving electricity consumption to a different interval of time, but total consumption remains constant.

Load Shifting with Battery Energy Storage Systems BESS - https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Battery_energy_storage_system 

